main event: The document provided is a Project Blue Book UFO report questionnaire filled out by a witness in Kettering, Ohio on 1st April 1954, lasting for 5 minutes. It includes details of the witness's observations, the conditions at the time of the sighting, and their personal details.
interesting points: The report includes a sketch of the observed object, described as spherical or oval-shaped, and labeled with an arrow indicating its movement.
The witness estimated the brightness of the object, compared its size to common objects held at arm's length, and described its color as whitish or white.
There's a section for the witness's opinion on what the object might have been and its possible cause, which was redacted.
The witness was asked if they had seen similar objects before and to provide details if they had, implying a recurring interest in UFO sightings.
The questionnaire requested the witness's personal details, including their job, age, and any special educational training they had.
